The paper focuses on developing a programming language and runtime system for service mobile robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic models and Bayesian inference for error detection and recovery, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper emphasizes the importance of non-expert users being able to program the robots, which involves human-robot interactions and usability considerations, making it relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the runtime system's ability to recover from errors, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the development of a programming language and runtime system, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
